            "id": "4404234",
            "title": "Stock index futures muted as job cuts jump, initial jobless claims come in hotter",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Stock index futures were muted on Thursday, and yields were largely flat as job cuts jumped in January over the prior month and initial jobless claims came in hotter.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">S&amp;P 500 futures (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPX\" title=\"S&amp;P 500 Index\">SPX</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+0.2%</span>, Nasdaq 100 futures (<a class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US100:IND\" title=\"NASDAQ 100 Futures\">US100:IND</a><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">) were unchanged</span><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" style=\"color: #ff0000;\">, </span><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">and Dow futures (</span><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper paywall-full-content invisible\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INDU\" title=\"Dow Jones Futures\">INDU</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">) </span><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\" style=\"color: #008000;\">+0.1%</span><span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">The 10-year Treasury yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US10Y\" title=\"United States 10-Year Bond Yield\">US10Y</a>) was unchanged at 4.44%. The 2-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US2Y\" title=\"United States 2-Year Bond Yield\">US2Y</a>) rose 1 basis point to 4.21%.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">Market sentiment took a hit after <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4403977-qualcomm-guidance-surpasses-estimates-as-smartphone-demand-drives-growth\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"QUALCOMM\">QUALCOMM</a> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/QCOM\" title=\"QUALCOMM Incorporated\">QCOM</a>) and <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4403981-fords-fy25-outlook-upstages-upbeat-q4-results\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Ford\">Ford</a> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/F\" title=\"Ford Motor Company\">F</a>) both fell over 4% after their earnings. </p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">Wall Street's major market averages closed higher Wednesday, overcoming earlier pressure brought on in part by a slump in shares of Magnificent Seven tech heavyweight Alphabet.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">\"After a severe allergic reaction on Monday after the tariff news, markets continued to be relatively sedated yesterday as investors continued to price out the chance of aggressive tariffs,\" Deutsche Bank's Jim Reid said.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">In terms of more detail on what drove the moves yesterday, the ISM services print added fuel to the bond rally, as the prices paid component fell back to 60.4, after spiking to 64.4 the previous month, Reid added. </p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">Labor reports take the spotlight in today's economic calendar.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">The number of <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4403799-january-job-cuts-climb-from-december-but-drop-from-a-year-ago-challenger\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"job cuts\">job cuts</a> announced by U.S. employers jumped 28% to 49,795 in January from December, but it fell 40% from January 2024, according to Challenger Gray &amp; Christmas data.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4404382-initial-jobless-claims-rise-more-than-expected-in-past-week\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Initial jobless claims\">Initial jobless claims</a> rose more than expected in the past week.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">The Q4 productivity and costs report will also be released before the market opens, and the Fed balance sheet will come in later in the day. </p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">\"U.S. productivity and unit labor cost data is important but not reliable in real time. Automation and technology should increase productivity over time, as will social trends,\" UBS' Paul Donovan said.</p> <p class=\"MsoNormal paywall-full-content invisible\">Tech will once again be under the radar, with <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4403576-amazon-q4-2024-earnings-preview\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" Amazon \">Amazon </a>(<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMZN\" title=\"Amazon.com, Inc.\">AMZN</a>) reporting its Q4 earnings after the bell. </p> </body></html>",
