            "id": "4404371",
            "title": "ArcelorMittal to build $900M steel plant in Alabama to meet U.S. auto sector demand",
            "description": "<html><body><p>ArcelorMittal (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MT\" title=\"ArcelorMittal S.A.\">MT</a></span>) said Thursday it plans to <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/markets/commodities/arcelormittal-build-new-steel-plant-us-meet-auto-sector-demand-2025-02-06/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_self\" title=\"build an advanced steel manufacturing facility\">build an advanced steel manufacturing facility</a> in Calvert, Alabama, to raise its production capacity to meet demand from the U.S. automotive sector.</p> <p>ArcelorMittal (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MT\" title=\"ArcelorMittal S.A.\">MT</a></span>) said the plant, estimated to cost $900M, would be able to<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> deliver up to 150 kt/year of premium non-grain-oriented electrical steel.</span></p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">The company said demand for sophisticated NOES in the U.S. is rising while domestic supplies are limited, which should support a premium pricing outlook for NOES produced at the new plant.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">\"If you include our mines in Canada, ~40% of our EBITDA is generated in North America, so we will continue to look for options to develop the business in the region,\" CFO Genuino Christino said on the earnings conference call.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">Christino estimated that potential tariffs would <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/markets/commodities/arcelormittal-plans-no-preemptive-us-steel-shipments-ahead-tariffs-cfo-says-2025-02-06/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_self\" title=\"cause a ~$100M hit per quarter\">cause a ~$100M hit per quarter</a> to the company, in line with analyst estimates, but if tariffs on Mexico are introduced, ArcelorMittal (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MT\" title=\"ArcelorMittal S.A.\">MT</a>) has the flexibility to reduce slab imports from there and increase them from Brazil instead.</p> <p class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\">ArcelorMittal (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MT\" title=\"ArcelorMittal S.A.\">MT</a>) <span style=\"color: #008000;\">+5.2%</span> pre-market Thursday after reporting its <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4404155-arcelormittal-misses-top-line-and-bottom-line-estimates-initiates-fy25-outlook\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Q4 net loss\">Q4 net loss</a> narrowed to $390M from a $2.97B loss in the year-earlier quarter when earnings were hurt by the disposal of its Kazakh operations and by an impairment charge related to Acciaierie d’Italia, and Q4 EBITDA jumped 14% Y/Y to $1.65B, compared with analyst estimates of a $319M net profit and $1.53B in EBITDA, according to a company-provided consensus.</p> </body></html>",
