            "title": "Gates Industrial beats top-line and bottom-line estimates; initiates Q1 outlook",
            "description": "<html><body><ul> <li>Gates Industrial <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/19994042-gates-industrial-reports-fourth-quarter-and-full-year-2024-results\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GTES\" title=\"Gates Industrial Corporation plc\">GTES</a></span>): Q4 Non-GAAP EPS of $0.36 <span class=\"green\"> beats by $0.03</span>.</li> <li>Revenue of $829.4M (-3.9% Y/Y) <span class=\"green\"> beats by $1.97M</span>.</li> <li>Adjusted EBITDA of $180.8 million, or a margin of 21.8%.</li> <li>Generated $379.6 million of operating cash flow.</li> <li><strong>Introducing 2025<span class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> financial guidance.</span></strong></li> <li class=\"paywall-full-content invisible\"> <p><strong>2025 Guidance</strong></p> <p>The Company is introducing full year financial guidance for 2025. Specifically, the company anticipates the following:</p> <ul> <li>Core sales growth in the range of (0.5%) to +3.5% year-over-year vs. estimated growth of 1.71% Y/Y.</li> <li>Adjusted EBITDA of $735 million to $795 million.</li> <li>Adjusted Earnings Per Share of $1.36 to $1.52 <strong>vs. $1.51 consensus.</strong> </li> <li>Capital Expenditures of approximately $120 million.</li> <li>Free Cash Flow conversion exceeding 90%.</li> </ul> </li> </ul> </body></html>",
